This will allow you to edit code in vim, textmate, sublime, or mvim. Once you've created some code, close the editor to have it run for you.
This works in IRB as well as Rails console

Running rake install will create the following files/folders:
~/.irb_plugins
~/.irb_plugins/open_editor.rb

and will edit/create your ~/.irbrc file to require that plugin

To uninstall:
rm ~/.irb_plugins/open_editor.rb
rmdir ~/.irb_plugins

Remove the following line from your ~/.irbrc
require '~/.irb_plugins/open_editor.rb'
